On the face of it, they might be against because they're going to lose power if they, if it, this is dropping out, Ward Representation Day, because there's, for example, no counselors from, I believe, South Medford.

845
01:21:13,892 --> 01:21:18,453
There's no counselors that live in West, East Medford, et cetera.

846
01:21:18,733 --> 01:21:21,013
There's parts of the city that aren't represented at all.

847
01:21:21,053 --> 01:21:22,874
And so they may or may not lose their,

848
01:21:24,314 --> 01:21:29,196
their district, or they will be several of them in one district and none in another.

849
01:21:29,616 --> 01:21:30,556
So they'll be running.

850
01:21:31,416 --> 01:21:36,918
It'll be changed the dynamics of the council and they may or may not like that.

851
01:21:37,578 --> 01:21:43,640
Also, if more counselors are added to the council we have a very small council compared to other cities.

852
01:21:44,340 --> 01:21:45,621
They might not like that either.

853
01:21:45,741 --> 01:21:47,864
They'll lose power because there'll be more counselors.

854
01:21:48,264 --> 01:21:57,994
So if in the race, we're asking them what their attitude is towards these issues, that's, I think, a very important thing.

855
01:21:58,955 --> 01:22:06,042
I think that's a great point to raise, to sort of bring these issues up in the city council race that's coming up.

856
01:22:07,362 --> 01:22:15,626
They are also changing, trying to change the charter a la carte by changing the budgetary process.

857
01:22:15,726 --> 01:22:17,967
That's a charter change in essence.

858
01:22:18,567 --> 01:22:35,454
And they're trying to just do it, whereas you guys are looking at the whole charter and the balance of power between the mayor in a holistic way, and they're doing a little a la carte, trying to do a little a la carte change, which is another issue that should be raised in the,

859
01:22:36,194 --> 01:22:42,199
because they're trying to basically get more power for the council without looking at the whole balance of power.

860
01:22:42,319 --> 01:22:52,348
And I think that's a very important issue also that should be raised in the city council race and questions should be asked.

861
01:22:53,989 --> 01:22:55,790
Those are my issue.

862
01:22:56,551 --> 01:22:56,871
Thank you.

863
01:22:58,313 --> 01:22:58,693
Thank you.

864
01:23:03,317 --> 01:23:04,558
Do we have anyone else on Zoom?

865
01:23:06,806 --> 01:23:08,927
Do we have any final questions or thoughts?

866
01:23:28,513 --> 01:23:29,153
Okay, sorry about that.

867
01:23:30,634 --> 01:23:34,216
So I'm in favor of definitely ward representation.

868
01:23:35,176 --> 01:23:36,757
I've been in this city for 20 years.

869
01:23:36,857 --> 01:23:39,499
I come from a city that has ward representation over in Malden.

870
01:23:40,179 --> 01:23:43,220
And then coming here, it was like, it was like a shock.

871
01:23:43,280 --> 01:23:46,542
I mean, you don't, there's no, there's no person to go to.

872
01:23:46,562 --> 01:23:55,587
You have a question, you email into a pool of seven people and hope that somebody returns your, you know, answers your question or whatever you have.

873
01:23:58,842 --> 01:23:59,883
not in their part of the city.

874
01:24:01,004 --> 01:24:04,166
There's so many benefits to having ward representation.

875
01:24:04,186 --> 01:24:06,188
It brings it down a little smaller.

876
01:24:06,208 --> 01:24:10,832
The ward counselor can do so many things in their little area.

877
01:24:10,872 --> 01:24:20,219
I know from Malden, every year there's some sort of a 4th of July in their little section, whoever is representing that.

878
01:24:20,299 --> 01:24:25,843
I'm not saying that, but they have their own little way of communicating with their

879
01:24:26,762 --> 01:24:27,042
ward.

880
01:24:27,082 --> 01:24:30,883
So I'm definitely in favor of ward representation.

881
01:24:31,483 --> 01:24:35,344
I know I can't speak as far as money.

882
01:24:35,704 --> 01:24:38,725
Council now gets like 30,000 or something in Malden.

883
01:24:39,385 --> 01:24:43,846
Each ward represents only it's a big jump.

884
01:24:45,266 --> 01:24:50,847
I think it's well worth looking into or definitely exploring ward representation.

885
01:24:51,027 --> 01:24:51,387
Thank you.

886
01:24:54,448 --> 01:24:54,668
Sorry.

887
01:24:57,805 --> 01:25:00,235
Any other thoughts or questions?

888
01:25:01,018 --> 01:25:01,379
Oh, great.

889
01:25:15,018 --> 01:25:20,841
Hi there, I am also in favor of ward representation combined with at-large.

890
01:25:21,021 --> 01:25:29,185
I like the model of having more representation with additional at-large kind of universal candidates.

891
01:25:29,225 --> 01:25:32,567
I think Somerville does this and I think it works very well.

892
01:25:32,707 --> 01:25:41,031
And then I wanna echo the in-person speaker who said building more transparency into this and timelines that allow for measured

893
01:25:43,355 --> 01:25:48,183
public comment and incorporating that knowledge into the process.

894
01:25:48,283 --> 01:25:52,009
None of this rushed budgeting at the last minute.

895
01:25:52,089 --> 01:25:54,433
I would like to see more presentation.

896
01:25:54,453 --> 01:25:56,957
Oh, somebody's vacuuming outside my office.

897
01:25:57,097 --> 01:25:57,398
Thank you.

898
01:25:59,127 --> 01:25:59,647
Thank you.

899
01:26:02,388 --> 01:26:13,411
When we heard from the Collins Center on city councils, we did learn that Medford is really in the very small minority, not having ward representation.

900
01:26:14,891 --> 01:26:22,293
And the hybrid model that Erica just referenced is by far the norm of a ward.

901
01:26:23,633 --> 01:26:28,479
Ward counselors and a few at large is the most common situation.

902
01:26:28,499 --> 01:26:32,885
So that's what we've learned so far about that.

903
01:26:34,787 --> 01:26:37,009
Any other questions or thoughts?

904
01:26:39,900 --> 01:26:47,544
Just on that point, Glenn Dixon, Monument Street, 61 Monument.

905
01:26:49,145 --> 01:26:57,970
The number of counselors for a city this size, is there any data on that as compared to other cities?

906
01:26:58,519 --> 01:27:06,928
Yeah, we are really the only, there are only, I believe, two other communities that have seven member councils and they're significantly smaller than Medford.

907
01:27:07,849 --> 01:27:10,792
So we really are an outlier in that regard as well.

908
01:27:14,776 --> 01:27:14,976
Yes.

909
01:27:17,953 --> 01:27:21,335
That's right, yes, we have eight wards.

910
01:27:21,355 --> 01:27:32,341
So we would have to enlarge the council and actually exclusively ward representation is probably not an option for Medford because we have an even number of wards.

911
01:27:33,622 --> 01:27:41,867
So you would be looking at a council of nine or 11 probably to go to ward.

912
01:27:57,065 --> 01:27:57,886
Um, that's all right.

913
01:27:58,167 --> 01:27:58,547
Thank you.

914
01:27:58,747 --> 01:28:00,049
Um, it could be done.

915
01:28:00,069 --> 01:28:06,377
I'm thinking I'm not politically astute on these things, and I don't like to make this as a comparison.

916
01:28:07,439 --> 01:28:12,485
This is why the original electoral college was found, because there are some states

917
01:28:13,346 --> 01:28:20,052
that have totally different landspans and different amount of populations than others.

918
01:28:20,712 --> 01:28:34,103
So if you do that in comparison, you may want to contact some people in other cities who have had a similar problem and how did they, if in fact they were able to, go to ward representation.

919
01:28:34,383 --> 01:28:40,148
In other words, ward one may have 500 residents, okay, and ward two may have 7,000.

920
01:28:41,749 --> 01:28:47,532
I mean, that's not a good comparison, but then one would have more than the other.

921
01:28:47,612 --> 01:28:51,533
So it would, seven could go to nine or nine could be 11.

922
01:28:51,873 --> 01:28:55,535
That's, I don't know if that would work, but I'm just making a suggestion.

923
01:28:57,167 --> 01:28:59,850
So that would be a little bit of population study.

924
01:29:00,250 --> 01:29:12,442
And it would change, but you could also go back and see also from public records and also from registration of voters what the percentage of change may be very, very minor from every two years or something.

925
01:29:13,576 --> 01:29:34,742
Yeah, I mean, the state does set the wards and there's also state, you know, I, I mean one question we asked at our last meeting was whether any, whether having sort of a counselor having word representation where you have four ward counselors and each counselor takes two wards and that's not really done.

926
01:29:34,762 --> 01:29:35,242
So that.

927
01:29:37,083 --> 01:29:39,765
You know, the question of that's not something that's done.

928
01:29:39,905 --> 01:29:47,669
And one of the things, when we talked about the state approving the charter, I mean, they're mostly looking at it to ensure that it complies with state law.

929
01:29:48,470 --> 01:29:50,291
That's the main reason they're looking at it.

930
01:29:50,891 --> 01:29:58,015
But when you put something in the charter that's unusual, they could question it.

931
01:29:58,835 --> 01:29:59,055
Right.

932
01:29:59,316 --> 01:30:04,018
But I think population would be a factor in that in different wads.

933
01:30:07,625 --> 01:30:17,693
From what we understand, the adjustments like that are not only way above our pay grade, but they're also done at the state level with the Secretary of State.

934
01:30:17,713 --> 01:30:21,837
So we don't have, we're not empowered to even suggest that would be your,

935
01:30:23,538 --> 01:30:27,479
the state legislation, it's a major, major project.

936
01:30:27,539 --> 01:30:38,442
We did receive the demographics description of each ward, and we'll use that because certainly diversity and representation is very, very important to us.

937
01:30:39,042 --> 01:30:43,164
But that is not part of what our charter would say.

938
01:30:43,504 --> 01:30:51,286
So we would have the option of keeping it at seven, or if we went to ward representation, just from what they've told us,

939
01:30:52,126 --> 01:30:53,626
we're looking at probably 11.

940
01:30:54,267 --> 01:31:01,529
Because if you had one additional at large, it doesn't promote candidates at large.

941
01:31:02,389 --> 01:31:05,550
So if I'm picking my ward, I'm going to be in my ward.

942
01:31:06,550 --> 01:31:10,311
But you have to really look at your ward and see how popular you are.

943
01:31:10,891 --> 01:31:13,813
then what's in it for me at large?

944
01:31:13,853 --> 01:31:23,839
That's why more people do three at large seats, just to justify an odd number of members and at the same time, an open election for more representation.

945
01:31:24,819 --> 01:31:31,323
But to answer your question with more words than I needed, it's way up here when they decide to change that.

946
01:31:31,483 --> 01:31:35,506
And, but we are looking at, we are looking at the demographics and we'll know what those are.

947
01:31:35,526 --> 01:31:47,073
And, and I think there's pluses and minuses, obviously word representation gives you diversity more than at large, but thanks.

948
01:31:48,934 --> 01:31:49,235
Thanks.

949
01:31:49,255 --> 01:31:50,135
We're going to zoom.

950
01:31:50,155 --> 01:31:50,596
Yeah.

951
01:32:04,862 --> 01:32:05,302
Marcia?

952
01:32:06,723 --> 01:32:08,724
Hi.

953
01:32:09,324 --> 01:32:17,369
I'd like to comment on this topic, too, because I do see the problem with wards and at large getting too big.

954
01:32:18,009 --> 01:32:32,177
And I think you should really take a serious look at rank choice voting, because it's my understanding that if you have maybe

955
01:32:32,927 --> 01:32:35,229
nine councils instead of 11.

956
01:32:36,350 --> 01:32:45,578
And I'm not sure how small it can be in actual work, but most people have a choice of theirs.

957
01:32:45,698 --> 01:32:57,189
It may not be the first choice, but one of the people they've chosen is on the council when they voted.

958
01:33:00,502 --> 01:33:02,903
Does everyone understand what it is?

959
01:33:05,425 --> 01:33:07,586
Or should I try to explain it?

960
01:33:14,570 --> 01:33:17,471
Is the question, do we know what rank choice voting is?

961
01:33:17,972 --> 01:33:18,232
Yes.

962
01:33:20,613 --> 01:33:21,894
Yes, we know.

963
01:33:22,074 --> 01:33:27,497
I think we might want to look at what it would be for Medford and how it might impact the city.

964
01:33:29,158 --> 01:33:34,631
So rank choice voting doesn't, it can be addressed in the charter, it doesn't have to be addressed in the charter.

965
01:33:36,999 --> 01:33:46,244
From what I have, from the information I have gathered, one of the issues about including it in our charter is that it's not done very much.

966
01:33:46,445 --> 01:33:50,247
It's not been instituted in very many communities in the state.

967
01:33:51,147 --> 01:33:56,551
And it's one of the issues that the state might flag.

968
01:33:56,791 --> 01:33:59,953
And we did have a state ballot question on it.

969
01:34:00,413 --> 01:34:01,874
And since Medford,

970
01:34:02,908 --> 01:34:04,588
Medford voted in favor.

971
01:34:04,728 --> 01:34:12,710
When you look at the breakdown of how Medford voted on rank choice voting, there was a majority, but it wasn't a large majority.

972
01:34:13,050 --> 01:34:22,552
And so we don't really know how the state would respond if that were put into the charter, but it has been raised here by more than one or two people.

973
01:34:22,592 --> 01:34:24,412
So it's definitely something we will look at.

974
01:34:26,372 --> 01:34:30,053
I think maybe it's not something that

975
01:34:31,245 --> 01:34:34,086
is immediately obvious to voters.

976
01:34:34,767 --> 01:34:40,789
And possibly the low response was because not everyone understood it yet.

977
01:34:42,470 --> 01:34:44,491
Although there could be many other reasons.

978
01:34:45,271 --> 01:34:46,132
They don't like it.

979
01:34:46,832 --> 01:34:47,312
I don't know.

980
01:34:47,332 --> 01:34:50,414
That's something to think about.

981
01:34:51,814 --> 01:34:56,416
What was the reason for the lower acceptance of it?

982
01:34:59,858 --> 01:35:00,218
Thank you.

983
01:35:06,180 --> 01:35:10,404
OK, do any committee members have any sort of final thoughts that they'd like to share?

984
01:35:10,424 --> 01:35:13,407
Anybody?

985
01:35:15,669 --> 01:35:15,889
Yes.

986
01:35:17,030 --> 01:35:18,892
Yes, thank you so much for coming.

987
01:35:20,113 --> 01:35:22,915
Yes, and please be in touch with us.

988
01:35:23,216 --> 01:35:25,077
Come to more of our meetings.

989
01:35:27,119 --> 01:35:29,781
And thanks again.

990
01:35:30,722 --> 01:35:31,083
Good night.

